			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Polyelectrolyte</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">聚电解质</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Polyelectrolyte gels; Cationic polyelectrolytes; Anionic polyelectrolytes; Polyelectrolyte multilayers (PEMs); Polyelectrolyte complex (PEC)</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Polyelectrolyte gels; Cationic polyelectrolytes; Anionic polyelectrolytes; Polyelectrolyte multilayers (PEMs); Polyelectrolyte complex (PEC)</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyelectrolyte gels are crosslinked ion-containing polymers with exceptional swelling capabilities, expanding up to 100 times in salt-free solutions. Their swelling is due to a balance between elasticity and osmotic pressure from counterions and salt ions. Cationic polyelectrolytes are positively charged and attract anions, while anionic ones are negatively charged and attract cations. They are used in flocculation, coagulation, and can respond to stimuli like pH, salt concentration, or electric fields.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚电解质凝胶是交联的含离子聚合物，具有非凡的溶胀能力，在无盐溶液中可膨胀100倍。它们的膨胀是由于反离子和盐离子的弹性和渗透压之间的平衡。阳离子聚电解质带正电并吸引阴离子，而阴离子聚电解质带负电并吸引阳离子。它们用于絮凝、混凝，可以对pH、盐浓度或电场等刺激做出反应。</common:generalComment>
